This paper focuses on predicting the virality of hashtags on social media platforms, which involves analyzing network properties, geographical properties, and conductance-related properties. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC), Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and Multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the emphasis on network analysis and social media data, cs.SI and cs.SOC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which could potentially place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, but this is less likely given the specific focus on social media and network analysis.
